The good: 
Love the movement controls....if you’ve ever driven a boat, they got pretty close. If you’re looking for precise, responsive controls....that’s not how boats work.

The bad:
Matchmaking, like many mobile games, isn’t balanced. Rarely do you see evenly-matched teams, and most matches are over quickly, with one team dominating the other. You’ll see level 8 boats matched against level 30, where they don’t stand a chance.

Horrible, horrible, horrible matchmaking.

Any PvP game makes it or breaks it on its matchmaking algorithm, and Battle Bay’s matchmaking algorithm is ATROCIOUS. Play a few matches and then look back over the scores: 90% of them will be 5-0, 5-1, 1-5, or 0-5. It’s almost like the developers have no idea how to construct fair, competitive matches with ships of comparable level. So prepare to either blow out your competition or get blown out instead. There appears to be no middle ground!
